reviewText: This movie has been great for my 2 and 4 year olds. Perfect for car rides since it last longer than most nick jr movies.

All these episodes air on Nick Jr. fairly regularly but the musical & dance themes throughout give the kids a good workout.  There is also a sing-along option which is very cool.  We played this on the big screen at my kid's birthday party since it had a dance theme and they loved it!  At $10 this is nice affordable addition to the library and a good way to drop the cable bill.

This is a great DVD for any preschool-aged Nickelodeon fan as it features all the best shows!  No commercials or missed shows, there is an episode for all six popular Nickelodeon characters.  While these episodes have previously aired on Nickelodeon my boys loved having them all on one DVD that they could watch anytime and anywhere.  It is a music and danced filled DVD with the episodes all focusing on fun!

The little ones haven't stopped dancing and singing to this DVD.  It is a bunch of episodes of the shows shown on the front cover.  It's not all dancing all the way through.  Still good but slightly misleading.
Boring! Just another movie. My kids never got up to dance. And they love love to dance

This DVD is NOT, I repeat, NOT a video for little ones to dance along with.  This is a compilation of 6 episodes of Nickelodeon TV shows that my 3 year old already had on our home DVR.  Each episode is music or dancing "related", but this is not at all what we expected.  We thought this may be interactive, maybe Dora would say "c'mon, get up and dance with me" or something of that nature....but this is just watching TV.  No music or sing/dance along motivation.  EXTREMELY disappointing.

I was expecting a lot more music in more if a music video type setting. Instead, it was episodes of different Nick cartoons. Only one episode really has a lot of music in it. My two year old loves two of the episodes and we watch those two and ignore the rest. I have them memorized. I was hoping for something that my daughter could sing along and dance to for the whole time, but we are satisfied with what we got instead. I think the title of the DVD is misleading.
